 that, when an average of these measurements is made, non-uniformities in
 the scale will tend to cancel.
 Also, you should avoid using the end of the meter stick which might be
 worn and, therefore, would not be a true zero.
 The apparent change in the reading on the scale due to the position of
 the eye is called parallax, an effect which can introduce error into the
